<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause xmlns:xt="urn:xpressauthor:trackchanges" id="_b1c4c7fe-ad29-4ebd-bd62-7281c9ca2003" outputclass="ncc-clause"><meta><facet building="Class 2"/><facet building="Class 3"/><facet building="Class 4"/><facet building="Class 5"/><facet building="Class 6"/><facet building="Class 7a"/><facet building="Class 7b"/><facet building="Class 8"/><facet building="Class 9a"/><facet building="Class 9b"/><facet building="Class 9c"/><facet building="Class 10b"/><facet building="Class 10c"/></meta><sptc>H4P6</sptc><title id="_88b084b9-14a5-4adb-aa89-e25fa9c3294b">Sound insulation</title><archive-num>2019: P2.4.6</archive-num><clause-variation href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/2053_3.1.0.xml" variation="NT" variation-type="REPLACE">NT REPLACE Clause</clause-variation><subclause id="_e5abc8e4-f396-40e8-a476-cf80c4701c06" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_67c3e43f-904b-40dc-a790-14d686fb809b">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>Walls separating dwellings must, to provide insulation against the transmission of airborne sound, have a weighted standardised level difference with spectrum adaptation term (D<sub id="_7aa3358a-8a65-4c26-9893-5da17cac68aa">nT</sub>,<sub id="_d5187805-adde-46b2-a478-298cd9ae02b3">w</sub>+C<sub id="_d01ed516-b387-4168-9cdd-021f3eb92089">tr</sub>) not less than 45.</p></subclause><subclause id="_162737b9-124f-4912-a1e7-7735f824d2b6" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_c8fbf79b-23af-41ce-9013-638c23e43acf">SubClause</title><num>2</num><p>Walls separating a bathroom, <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1445_0.13.0.xml#_b30a308f-eb9f-4549-a6c1-19d5f32a5272" id="_bcd667ff-79a4-4575-86ac-bf0696643400" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">sanitary compartment</xref>, laundry or kitchen in a dwelling from a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1326_0.4.0.xml#_b8eec66f-9c05-425d-8474-e6a2dfc2c0f4" id="_11fefb65-d427-44f7-84a7-65dfa4e022d9" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">habitable room</xref> (other than a kitchen) in an adjoining dwelling, must provide insulation against impact generated sound sufficient to prevent illness or loss of <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1186_0.6.0.xml#_905252bf-2ff1-43f8-ae81-2949aa116fee" id="_ab167ef8-bff8-4633-a436-ec490410e2b7" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">amenity</xref> to the occupants.</p></subclause><subclause id="_e3f29969-e864-4268-9541-e79e8bc2686e" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_390bd743-7479-4bd0-91fa-d29daba705cf">SubClause</title><num>3</num><p>The <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1432_4.0.0.xml#_af6fde9f-147d-4782-8b85-42044e80fd42" id="_5b0c7265-fa81-4ad9-9713-c38681ae579f" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">required</xref> sound insulation of walls must not be compromised by the incorporation or penetration of a pipe or other service element.</p></subclause></clause>